<subSubSection id="E9031900084200A52EF431EE1D65A5FC" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" type="differential diagnosis">
<paragraph id="F6E3F53865ADD1AE33570B02A6B76E11" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Differential diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0AC3A19EDDDB8F5FF2B08DD65F3BEB93" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
Second tergum with a broad macula reaching apical 1/2. Third tergum with a short rounded basal fascia. Metacoxa black pilose. 
<taxonomicName id="AA3B221E0AADCA9FB82956BFFF508036" authorityName="Montoya" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Argentinomyia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Argentinomyia huitepecensis" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="huitepecensis">
<emphasis id="24CD56A8CCE2286D78D7902304D3B688" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Argentinomyia huitepecensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="BC70A390472E0A9980F90CA3079A8EB9" genus="A." lsidName="A. puntarena" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" rank="species" species="puntarena">
<emphasis id="FB1B0F7BD3A04CC6FAFB9F6F935ED809" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">A. puntarena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov., but differs from it by having the antenna oval, longer than wide, orange ventrally; alula and costal cell bare; pro- and mesofemur yellow; metafemur orange on basal 1/5 and apical 3/5; pro, meso- and metabasitarsomere I-II yellow. 
<taxonomicName id="3EB4387036485FC7E17389D54E430733" authorityName="Montoya" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Argentinomyia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Argentinomyia huitepecensis" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="huitepecensis">
<emphasis id="9AF704E5FC2EA2B85C5F23A2C448C937" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Argentinomyia huitepecensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. is also similar to 
<taxonomicName id="51A68E7EF8BAFE962E31163C938CA173" genus="A." lsidName="A. talamanca" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" rank="species" species="talamanca">
<emphasis id="3180B6AFB49D753EDF17AEB0A203AF00" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">A. talamanca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. a species with the antenna brown; alula and costal cell extensively microtrichose; femur extensively brown; the second tergum with a pair of small maculae on basal 1/5 (see 'diagnostic 
<normalizedToken id="EDCA17C1258025159C81655710AADF7D" originalValue="features’">features'</normalizedToken>
under each species or key).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
